Package: conCultuR
Title: Measurement Framework for Conservation Culturomics and Biodiversity Attention
Version: 0.8.6
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yuno", "Do", email = "doyunho@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Implements a reproducible measurement framework for conservation culturomics. The package helps users construct biodiversity concept dictionaries, audit query ambiguity, collect or simulate digital attention traces from heterogeneous platforms, standardise platform-specific signals, estimate biodiversity attention indices, quantify attention gaps relative to threat status, diagnose platform disagreement and query sensitivity, evaluate campaign-associated attention deviations, and summarise narrative frames. The package is designed as a methodological workflow for transparent biodiversity-attention measurement rather than as a single-platform application programming interface wrapper.
